translate ru strings:

    old "Unable to get to sleep, Sarah had taken to wandering the camp."
    new "Unable to get to sleep, Sarah had taken to wandering the camp."

    old "All around the lake that she had drawn from the earth, there were now small improvised encampments."
    new "All around the lake that she had drawn from the earth, there were now small improvised encampments."

    old "In a few, a campfire still burned, in others, only the embers were left."
    new "In a few, a campfire still burned, in others, only the embers were left."

    old "Here and there, Sarah could hear the murmurs of festivities drawing to an end. Here and there, the sounds of bodies connecting."
    new "Here and there, Sarah could hear the murmurs of festivities drawing to an end. Here and there, the sounds of bodies connecting."

    old "Sarah ignored it all, weaving through the darkness between the camps."
    new "Sarah ignored it all, weaving through the darkness between the camps."

    old "She wanted to be alone for a while."
    new "She wanted to be alone for a while."

    old "Alone with her own thoughts."
    new "Alone with her own thoughts."

    old "Though the soldiers of the mercenary company had taken the lake for the miracle that it was, and had thrown plenty of praise on her, Sarah still struggled with it."
    new "Though the soldiers of the mercenary company had taken the lake for the miracle that it was, and had thrown plenty of praise on her, Sarah still struggled with it."

    old "The voice that had moved her to strike the earth and draw forth the water..."
    new "The voice that had moved her to strike the earth and draw forth the water..."

    old "How could such a thing be."
    new "How could such a thing be."

    old "Slowly, Sarah made her way up the flank of one of the dunes."
    new "Slowly, Sarah made her way up the flank of one of the dunes."

    old "From the elevated position, she could look out across the camp and its few remaining lights."
    new "From the elevated position, she could look out across the camp and its few remaining lights."

    old "Turning around in the other direction, Sarah saw the stretching desert, reaching all the way to the horizon."
    new "Turning around in the other direction, Sarah saw the stretching desert, reaching all the way to the horizon."

    old "A gust of wind rushed past her, across her naked body, the cold taking root in her."
    new "A gust of wind rushed past her, across her naked body, the cold taking root in her."

    old "She oddly welcomed the cold."
    new "She oddly welcomed the cold."

    old "Behind her, the camp was quiet. Gone was the simmering resentment that had hung over them like a cloud."
    new "Behind her, the camp was quiet. Gone was the simmering resentment that had hung over them like a cloud."

    old "Sarah drew in a deep breath, taking in the desert air."
    new "Sarah drew in a deep breath, taking in the desert air."

    old "Looking out across the vast space, she imagined that it looked little different from the desert at any other point since leaving Bagrad."
    new "Looking out across the vast space, she imagined that it looked little different from the desert at any other point since leaving Bagrad."

    old "If not for the pain in her muscles and the sores on her feet, she could have imagined that they had barely moved at all."
    new "If not for the pain in her muscles and the sores on her feet, she could have imagined that they had barely moved at all."

    old "A darkness stood out."
    new "A darkness stood out."

    old "For a moment, in the moonlit night of the desert, it had appeared as an oddity, but slowly Sarah felt her eyes drawn to it."
    new "For a moment, in the moonlit night of the desert, it had appeared as an oddity, but slowly Sarah felt her eyes drawn to it."

    old "A darkness that was more like a void, filled with starlight"
    new "A darkness that was more like a void, filled with starlight"

    old "Black as ink."
    new "Black as ink."

    old "The more she looked, the more Sarah felt herself drawn to it, and in turn, the greater it appeared to be and become."
    new "The more she looked, the more Sarah felt herself drawn to it, and in turn, the greater it appeared to be and become."

    old "Rising."
    new "Rising."

    old "From the emptiness of the desert, a pitch-black emptiness began to rise."
    new "From the emptiness of the desert, a pitch-black emptiness began to rise."

    old "Sarah could feel her breath, catching in her throat as the thing contiued to grow, rising up far above the horizon."
    new "Sarah could feel her breath, catching in her throat as the thing contiued to grow, rising up far above the horizon."

    old "Soon, the thing pierced the sky itself, contrasted against the backdrop of the world."
    new "Soon, the thing pierced the sky itself, contrasted against the backdrop of the world."

    old "Sarah felt a jolt in her body."
    new "Sarah felt a jolt in her body."

    old "And the world resumed itself."
    new "And the world resumed itself."

    old "As sudden as the pillar had appeared, so instantly had it vanished."
    new "As sudden as the pillar had appeared, so instantly had it vanished."

    old "And the world was back as it had been, except, now the absence of the void appeared in itself to be odd. As if the natural world was itself now lacking something."
    new "And the world was back as it had been, except, now the absence of the void appeared in itself to be odd. As if the natural world was itself now lacking something."

    old "Sarah raised up her hands to her breasts and felt herself breathing, her chest rising and falling."
    new "Sarah raised up her hands to her breasts and felt herself breathing, her chest rising and falling."

    old "She knew she was awake."
    new "She knew she was awake."

    old "She knew the thing had been real."
    new "She knew the thing had been real."

    old "And Sarah knew, though she could not say how, where the city of Nauyziri rested."
    new "And Sarah knew, though she could not say how, where the city of Nauyziri rested."

